      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARTAY (1) bolted in two back before a 0.6L defeat at Belmont when an odds-on favourite. Back to 1400m today may be the query, but the claim of Cooper comes in handy and he should be prominent from the outset. Looks a talented gelding and can continue to work through the grades. REBELS (9) led them up over 1300m at Pinjarra last start and stuck on well. This is tougher, but the rise to 1400m looks to suit better and he carries no weight after the claim of Webster. Can sit handy and be in this for a long way. AWESOME FORCE (3) is third-up today after getting well back last start at Pinjarra and closing off solidly. He'll be better for that effort though and he showed good improvement from his first run to last start. Can improve again third-up. UNGOVERNED (6) won't be far away. MYSTERIOUS FORTUNE (5) can be in the finish on the quick turnaround.",
